Detailed Description

LibraryData is the data model that manages the actual VLNV library.

This class reads and saves the library file in file system and provides services to manage the library. This class also provides model for a table view so contents of the library can be viewed.

void LibraryData::updateVLNV ( const QString &  path,
const VLNV &  newVLNV 
)

Update the VLNV for the given document.

If the library does not contain the given vlnv yet it is added to the library. Note: Although it is possible, this function should not be used to add new items to the library because it may be slow (linear time). This function should be used to change the vlnv of an existing document.

Parameters:
path The path to the document in the file system.
newVLNV The new vlnv for the document.
